// Typst article template with formal requirements for Network Neuroscience.
// Edit the placeholders in the Template section and keep this file as a
// single source of truth for submission constraints.

#set page(numbering: "1")
#set text(font: "Times New Roman", size: 12pt, leading: 1.8em)

= Template

#let article-type = "Research"
#let running-head = "Shortened title for running head (optional)"

#align(center)[
  #text(size: 10pt)[Article type: #article-type]
  #text(size: 18pt, weight: "bold")[Title of the article (max 350 chars)]
  #text(size: 12pt, style: "italic")[Subtitle (optional)]
  #text(size: 10pt)[Short title (max 70 chars): #running-head]
  #text(size: 10pt)[Authors with affiliations (use superscripts)]
  #text(size: 10pt)[Affiliations list]
  #text(size: 10pt)[Corresponding author: name, email]
  #text(size: 10pt)[Keywords: up to 6, comma-separated]
]

== Abstract (max 200 words)
Write the abstract here.

== Author Summary (Research and Focus only, max 125 words)
Write the author summary here.

== Introduction
Write the introduction here. Do not use subheadings in the Introduction.

== Results
Write the results here.

== Discussion
Write the discussion here.

== Materials and Methods
Write the methods here.

== Acknowledgements
Write the acknowledgements here.

== Supporting Information (optional)
Provide any supporting information referenced in the manuscript. Submit as
separate PDFs in a format ready to publish.

== Competing Interests (optional)
If you declared a conflict of interest at submission, provide details here.

== References
Provide complete references. APA format required at revision stage.

== Technical Terms
Bold the first occurrence of each technical term in the text. Provide around
10 terms with brief (20 words or less) definitions after the references.

*Technical Term* Definition of the term in plain language.

*Technical Term* Definition of the term in plain language.
